During the Russian Civil War the UNOVIS group centered on Kasimir Malevich and Lissitzky designed various projects that forced together the ' non - objective ' abstraction of Suprematism with more utilitarian aims , creating ideal Constructivist cities— see also El Lissitzky 's " Prounen - Raum " , the ' Dynamic City ' ( 1919 ) of Gustav Klutsis ; Lazar Khidekel 's Workers Club ( 1926 ) and his Dubrovka Power Plant and first Sots Town ( 1931–33 ) .
